Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a new PRNG suitable for cryptographic applications and evaluates its robustness against attacks. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the statistical properties of the proposed PRNG and its ability to pass statistical tests. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper uses chaotic iterations to improve the randomness of the PRNG, which is a topic related to systems and control. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new algorithm for generating random numbers using chaotic iterations and XORshifts. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper presents an illustration of the proposed PRNG in the field of data hiding, which is a topic related to multimedia.
